/*
optimized version of this problem :

we need to remember a trick for this

as we know we need to add 1 from l till r
so what we will do is: add 1 at index l and -1 at index r+1

and will do prefix sum of the array
eg: l=3 r=4

   0,0,0,0,0
   0 0 1 0 -1
prefix sum: 0 0 1 1 0
this is our answer.

we can do this for multiple queries at once.

eg : l=3 r=7
     l=5 r=8
index:                  1 2 3 4 5 6 7  8   9
initially:              0,0,0,0,0,0,0, 0,  0
inserting 1 and -1:     0 0 1 0 0 1 0 -1  -1
prefix sum:             0 0 1 1 1 2 2  1   0

This is our final answer.


if r==arr.length then we should increase array length by 1 as we need to put -1 in index r+1



so we can put 1 and -1 for each query in O(1) time
and then calculate prefix sum of the full array to get our answer.

this is not a trick but a concept called "difference array technique"



IMPORTANT CONCEPT:

when we see same task again and again for a range then we can apply this concept.




 */


public class _04_visaOA_print_arr_after_operations {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        int[] arr=new int[n+2];

        int q=sc.nextInt();

        int[] prefixSum=new int[n+2];
        prefixSum[0]=0;
        int i=1;
        while(i<=q){
            int l=sc.nextInt();
            int r=sc.nextInt();

            arr[l]+=1;
            arr[r+1]-=1;
            i++;

        }
        for(int k=1;k<prefixSum.length-1;k++){
            prefixSum[k]=prefixSum[k-1]+arr[k];
        }
        for(int j=1;j<prefixSum.length-1;j++){
            System.out.print(prefixSum[j]+" ");
        }
    }
}



//time comp: O(N)+O(Q)
